            <title>[PIG-2590] running ant tar and rpm targets on same copy of pig source results in problems</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2590</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If &quot;ant tar&quot; is run, followed by &quot;ant rpm&quot; then the tar.gz that was generated gets overwritten by an intermediate tar.gz used by the rpm install&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Running both of them results in  duplicate files in the 2nd one, because both use the same staging directory before packaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
